				\begin{document}$$N{h}^{2}/M+{Na}+1$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M160"><mml:mi>N</mml:mi><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>/</mml:mo><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mi>N</mml:mi><mml:mi>a</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2022_35328_Article_IEq58.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> as described in Bulik-Sullivan et al.<sup><xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR22">22</xref></sup>. Note that the inflation term <italic>Na</italic> is simplified as <italic>I</italic> in (10) and true effect term <inline-formula id="IEq59"><alternatives><tex-math id="M161">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$N{h}^{2}/M$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M162"><mml:mi>N</mml:mi><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>/</mml:mo><mml:mi>M</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2022_35328_Article_IEq59.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is simplified as <italic>pΛ</italic> in (10). Next, <italic>I</italic> (or inflation factor <italic>s</italic>=<italic>I</italic>+1) can be determined using an iterative search algorithm with the moments of <bold>T</bold> and a series of quantiles of <bold>T</bold> <inline-formula id="IEq60"><alternatives><tex-math id="M163">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
